name: "The Collector"
description:
This is a fun shade made up of an old coffee sack, vintage keys, vintage GE fan cover and my original artwork printed on organic fabric for the bird detail. 

After machine stitching the details to the coffee sack, the material was hand stitched to the metal frame.

name: Red Cross Lamp Shade
description:
This shade is part of my distress series and is titled "Red Cross".  

The shade is hand constructed using washed cotton canvas and red cotton fabric.  An upholstery zipper detail was added at the top of the shade and then the design was hand stitched  to the metal frame.

The shade measures approx. 17"H x 15"W

name: Rescue Me Lamp Shade
description:
This shade is part of my distress series and is titled "Rescue Me".  

The shade is hand constructed using washed cotton canvas and red cotton fabric.  The words "Rescue Me" are machined stitched into the design and the fabric was hand stitched to the metal frame.

The shade measures approx. 17"H x 15"W

name: Sprinkle Flowers Trifle Bowl
description:
Using an art form that dates back to the 12th century, Decoupage, a print of my original art is applied on the inside of a clear glass trifle bowl.

The motif was derived from my original painting called "Sprinkles".  After carefully cutting out the design I applied the print to the inside of the bowl.  To finish off the inside, a few coats of paint were added and then sealed with professional grade artist mediums.  The top rim is detailed in gold leaf.

This trifle bowl is for decorative purposes only and is not food safe.

name: BluePrint One
description:
Original Mixed Media on Canvas
4" x 12"

A Blueprint of a building I worked on many years ago was part of the mixed media used in this original work of art.  (This was before drawings were produced with AutoCAD ; ) )

name: Vintage Nature Chair
description:
I found this chair at a local antique store and just loved the style but the original fabric was in bad shape.  So . . . I went in search of some beautiful fabric to bring it back to life.  I decided to hand applique a moth motif, (that came from a fabric that was covered in insects), onto a green linen fabric and then took it to my upholster to put it all together.  LOVE the way it all came together.

***Local Pick-Up Only*****
